Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
In order to cross a street, you need to make sure you can safe. Look left and right to see if there are cars in either way. Usually, the car will stops for you. If there is a traffic light, then you need to follow the traffic light. Only walk when it is not red. Remember that you need to across the street through the pedestrian path.